Wonderful.

00:53:30.170 --> 00:53:32.680
Oh yeah, so pre-Arab Spring--

00:53:32.680 --> 00:53:35.080
so a lot of artists depicted
a lot of political events,

00:53:35.080 --> 00:53:39.210
including the destruction
of Iraq in the 1991 war.

00:53:39.210 --> 00:53:43.110
Here, you see one of the
sculpture of Ishtar crying.

00:53:43.110 --> 00:53:48.690
The red flag, the angel,
has had its limbs cut off.

00:53:48.690 --> 00:53:51.930
This is poster by a Kuwaiti
that became a stencil

00:53:51.930 --> 00:53:55.350
during the occupation of Saddam
forces of Kuwait in 1991.

00:53:55.350 --> 00:53:56.710
I love these two works.

00:53:56.710 --> 00:53:58.410
This is an artist
called Walid Ebeid

00:53:58.410 --> 00:54:01.050
who depicted a lot of the
events in Egypt that really

00:54:01.050 --> 00:54:03.510
led to the uprising of 2011.

00:54:03.510 --> 00:54:05.260
In this case, he shows
you the bread line.

00:54:05.260 --> 00:54:09.490
So one of the slogans of the
Egyptian uprising of 2011 was

00:54:09.490 --> 00:54:10.740
[NON-ENGLISH], which is bread.

00:54:10.740 --> 00:54:11.760
So people wanted bread.

00:54:11.760 --> 00:54:13.560
So here, he's showing
you the bread lines

00:54:13.560 --> 00:54:16.920
as far back as 2005, and
this is not the first time

00:54:16.920 --> 00:54:19.200
that riots erupted in
Egypt because of bread.

00:54:19.200 --> 00:54:21.870
So you see here, a lot of
these people standing in line.

00:54:21.870 --> 00:54:23.910
They have cash in
hand, but there isn't

00:54:23.910 --> 00:54:25.420
enough bread for everybody.

